article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 85, W. Illinois 71
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Junior Derick Nelson scored a game high 18 points to lead Oakland 85-71 over Western Illinois Saturday night. Brandon Cassise scored 15, including three 3-pointers and eight assists, and Keith Benson had 14 points on 5-of-5 shooting for the Golden Grizzlies (10-10, 5-4 Summit). Two other players scored in the double-digits for Oakland. Johnathon Jones had 11 points and Tim Williams came off the bench and chipped in another 11. Oakland led 42-36 at the half and never trailed. The Golden Grizzlies shot 29-of-42 from the field or 69 percent, compared with the Leathernecks' 27-for-59, or about 46 percent. David Jackson had 16 points, including three assists, for Western Illinois (9-11, 4-5). Louis Johnson came off the bench and scored 12 points, including six rebounds, on 5-of-5 shooting. David Nurse had 11 points and David DuBois chipped in 10 points.
